  <description/>
  <content:encoded><![CDATA[<!-- wp:cover {"url":"https://shishukunjmun4.files.wordpress.com/2023/05/istockphoto-986035072-1024x1024-transformed.jpeg","id":1221,"dimRatio":50,"minHeight":680,"contentPosition":"center center","isDark":false,"align":"full","style":{"spacing":{"padding":{"right":"var:preset|spacing|60","left":"var:preset|spacing|60"}}},"layout":{"type":"default"}} -->
<div class="wp-block-cover alignfull is-light" style="padding-right:var(--wp--preset--spacing--60);padding-left:var(--wp--preset--spacing--60);min-height:680px"><span aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-cover__background has-background-dim"></span><img class="wp-block-cover__image-background wp-image-1221" alt="" src="https://shishukunjmun4.files.wordpress.com/2023/05/istockphoto-986035072-1024x1024-transformed.jpeg" data-object-fit="cover" /><div class="wp-block-cover__inner-container"><!-- wp:columns -->
<div class="wp-block-columns"><!-- wp:column {"verticalAlignment":"center"} -->
<div class="wp-block-column is-vertically-aligned-center"><!-- wp:group {"layout":{"type":"flex"}} -->
<div class="wp-block-group"><!-- wp:site-logo {"width":166} /--></div>
<!-- /wp:group --></div>
<!-- /wp:column -->

<!-- wp:column {"verticalAlignment":"center","width":"1054px"} -->
<div class="wp-block-column is-vertically-aligned-center" style="flex-basis:1054px"><!-- wp:group {"layout":{"type":"flex","flexWrap":"nowrap","justifyContent":"right"}} -->
<div class="wp-block-group"><!-- wp:navigation {"ref":1011,"textColor":"background","showSubmenuIcon":false,"icon":"menu","layout":{"type":"flex","justifyContent":"right","orientation":"horizontal","flexWrap":"wrap"},"style":{"layout":{"selfStretch":"fill","flexSize":null},"spacing":{"blockGap":"var:preset|spacing|50"},"typography":{"fontSize":"1rem"}}} /--></div>
<!-- /wp:group --></div>
<!-- /wp:column --></div>
<!-- /wp:columns -->

<!-- wp:spacer {"height":"53px"} -->
<div style="height:53px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<!-- /wp:spacer -->

<!-- wp:heading {"textAlign":"center","style":{"typography":{"fontSize":"2.6rem"}}} -->
<h2 class="wp-block-heading has-text-align-center" style="font-size:2.6rem"><mark style="background-color:rgba(0, 0, 0, 0)" class="has-inline-color has-background-color"><strong>F</strong>OOD AND <strong>A</strong>GRICULTURE <strong>O</strong>RGANIZATION 2</mark></h2>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:paragraph {"align":"center","style":{"typography":{"fontSize":"1.2rem"}}} -->
<p class="has-text-align-center" style="font-size:1.2rem"><mark style="background-color:rgba(0, 0, 0, 0);color:#cecbcc" class="has-inline-color"><strong>Agenda</strong>: Tackling Food Insecurity and Deficits in Agriculture</mark></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:spacer {"height":"153px"} -->
<div style="height:153px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<!-- /wp:spacer --></div></div>
<!-- /wp:cover -->

<!-- wp:heading {"textAlign":"center","lock":{"move":true,"remove":true},"style":{"typography":{"fontSize":"2.4rem"}},"textColor":"vivid-cyan-blue"} -->
<h2 class="wp-block-heading has-text-align-center has-vivid-cyan-blue-color has-text-color" style="font-size:2.4rem"><strong>Letter From The Chairperson</strong></h2>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:group {"align":"wide","layout":{"type":"flex","orientation":"vertical","verticalAlignment":"center","justifyContent":"center"}} -->
<div class="wp-block-group alignwide"><!-- wp:image {"id":4807,"width":265,"height":325,"scale":"cover","sizeSlug":"large","linkDestination":"none"} -->
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large is-resized"><img src="https://shishukunjmun4.files.wordpress.com/2023/07/mansha-1.jpg?w=871" alt="" class="wp-image-4807" style="object-fit:cover;width:265px;height:325px" width="265" height="325" /></figure>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:group {"style":{"layout":{"selfStretch":"fixed","flexSize":"700px"}},"layout":{"type":"flex","orientation":"vertical","verticalAlignment":"top","justifyContent":"left"}} -->
<div class="wp-block-group"><!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Dear delegates,</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>With immense pleasure, I welcome each one of you to the first Junior Shishukunj Model United Nations Conference. I, Mansha Sharangpani, am pleased to serve as the chairperson of the Food and Agriculture Organisation 2.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>I am an eleventh grader studying Commerce with Applied Mathematics. Todays world seeks a versatile youth. Its not solely knowledge that builds ones personality. Various skills and talents play an equally important role. Following this, I was driven to participate in Model United Nations conferences. I have been participating in MUNs for the past 4 years and they have not only enhanced my knowledge about the world but made me much more confident than before. I am a skilful artist and love digital designing. If not scramming books you will find me saying Alexa, play Spotify and sketching masterpieces or mingling with my friends. I am a great problem solver and enjoy connecting with people, so feel free to reach out to me.&nbsp;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Have you ever wondered why we were stopped while dumping the uneaten food in the lunch hall? Well, in the present time, millions of people go on living for days without eating food. Our agenda emphasises the state of these undernourished people and the problems faced in agriculture. Improper amounts of nutritious food lead to Food insecurity, wherein people remain hungry for days. It stands as a significant global concern and thus is a great agenda to be discussed. The goal of the committee is to come up with efficient solutions to deal with hunger caused by food insecurity and problems that prevail in agriculture.&nbsp;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Delegates, Model United Nations conferences are a great platform for integrated learning and personality development. I hope this conference is full of fun, excitement, and learning for all of you, looking forward to meeting you all this August as wonderful delegates.&nbsp;All the best!&nbsp;<br><br>Regards,<br><strong>Mansha Sharangpani&nbsp;</strong><br><strong>Chairperson</strong><br><strong>FAO 2</strong></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph --></div>
<!-- /wp:group --></div>
<!-- /wp:group -->

<!-- wp:separator {"lock":{"move":true,"remove":true},"align":"wide","className":"is-style-wide"} -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator alignwide has-alpha-channel-opacity is-style-wide" />
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:heading {"textAlign":"left","lock":{"move":true,"remove":true},"align":"wide","style":{"typography":{"fontSize":"2.4rem"}},"textColor":"vivid-cyan-blue"} -->
<h2 class="wp-block-heading alignwide has-text-align-left has-vivid-cyan-blue-color has-text-color" style="font-size:2.4rem"><strong>Organ Description</strong></h2>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:group {"align":"wide","layout":{"type":"default"}} -->
<div class="wp-block-group alignwide"><!-- wp:paragraph {"align":"left"} -->
<p class="has-text-align-left">The food and agriculture organization (FAO) is a specialized agency that was founded in 1945. The main purpose of FAO is to achieve food security all over the world and eliminate hunger. FAO plays a central role in enhancing nutrition and improving agricultural productivity. Other than this, it aims to develop areas like fisheries, forestry and water and&nbsp; land related resources. The FAO works to administer sustainable food supplies, resources and operational systems rather than just providing food or aid.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:separator {"align":"wide","className":"is-style-wide"} -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator alignwide has-alpha-channel-opacity is-style-wide" />
<!-- /wp:separator --></div>
<!-- /wp:group -->

<!-- wp:heading {"textAlign":"left","lock":{"move":true,"remove":true},"align":"wide","style":{"typography":{"fontSize":"2.4rem"}},"textColor":"vivid-cyan-blue"} -->
<h2 class="wp-block-heading alignwide has-text-align-left has-vivid-cyan-blue-color has-text-color" style="font-size:2.4rem"><strong>Agenda : Tackling Food Insecurity and Deficits in Agriculture</strong></h2>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:group {"align":"wide","layout":{"type":"default"}} -->
<div class="wp-block-group alignwide"><!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Food is one of the important substances for the sustenance of life. The state of lacking proper nutritious food in sufficient amounts is called Food Insecurity. Food insecurity is faced by millions of people around the world, and thus is a global crisis that needs to be resolved. Food insecurity leads to undernourishment, a form of malnutrition. Undernourishment is often referred to as hunger, a painful sensation faced by a person when he/ she skips meals or goes on for days without eating. Food insecurity has several causes, some of them being poverty, gender inequality, and food wastage. Hunger is directly related to food insecurity. Food insecurity in a nation is also surged by the sudden attack of natural calamities. Natural calamities which lead to a rise in food insecurity majorly include hurricanes, floods, tsunamis, earthquakes, landslides, and droughts. In the present time, there are several barriers which affect a proper produce in agriculture. Since the green revolution, to prevent environmental degradation humans have come up with organic farming. But, organic farming still has some problems which need to be resolved, these include lower yields, inefficiency of equipment etc. Apart from this, soil degradation stands as a major deficit in agriculture that needs to be taken care of. Soil plays an important role in agriculture. It is degraded by humans in many ways like overgrazing, mining, and over irrigation.&nbsp;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>The deficits in agriculture ultimately lead to a lower produce and indirectly cause a rise in food insecurity in the nation. The prevailing food insecurity in several nations will lead to rise in diseases and mortality rate and also affect childrens growth and development. This is the grim reality that several people have to face and this global crisis needs to be looked after.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph --></div>
<!-- /wp:group -->

<!-- wp:separator {"align":"wide","className":"is-style-wide"} -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator alignwide has-alpha-channel-opacity is-style-wide" />
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:columns -->
<div class="wp-block-columns"><!-- wp:column -->
<div class="wp-block-column"><!-- wp:image {"id":1219,"width":247,"height":250,"sizeSlug":"large","linkDestination":"custom"} -->
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large is-resized"><img src="https://shishukunjmun4.files.wordpress.com/2023/05/fao_logo.svg_.png?w=640" alt="" class="wp-image-1219" style="width:247px;height:250px" width="247" height="250" /><figcaption class="wp-element-caption"><strong>Study Guide</strong></figcaption></figure>
<!-- /wp:image --></div>
<!-- /wp:column -->

<!-- wp:column -->
<div class="wp-block-column"><!-- wp:image {"id":3032,"width":211,"height":243,"sizeSlug":"large","linkDestination":"custom"} -->
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large is-resized"><a href="https://shishukunjmun4.files.wordpress.com/2023/07/fao2.pdf"><img src="https://shishukunjmun4.files.wordpress.com/2023/06/pdf_file_icon.svg_.png?w=640" alt="" class="wp-image-3032" style="width:211px;height:243px" width="211" height="243" /></a><figcaption class="wp-element-caption"><strong>Allotments</strong></figcaption></figure>

<!-- wp:column {"verticalAlignment":"center","width":"1054px"} -->
<div class="wp-block-column is-vertically-aligned-center" style="flex-basis:1054px"><!-- wp:group {"layout":{"type":"flex","flexWrap":"nowrap","justifyContent":"right"}} -->
<div class="wp-block-group"><!-- wp:navigation {"ref":1011,"textColor":"background","showSubmenuIcon":false,"icon":"menu","layout":{"type":"flex","justifyContent":"right","orientation":"horizontal","flexWrap":"wrap"},"style":{"layout":{"selfStretch":"fill","flexSize":null},"spacing":{"blockGap":"var:preset|spacing|50"},"typography":{"fontSize":"1rem"}}} /--></div>
<!-- /wp:group --></div>
<!-- /wp:column --></div>
<!-- /wp:columns -->

<!-- wp:spacer {"height":"52px"} -->
<div style="height:52px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<!-- /wp:spacer -->

<!-- wp:heading {"textAlign":"center","style":{"typography":{"fontSize":"2.6rem"}}} -->
<h2 class="wp-block-heading has-text-align-center" style="font-size:2.6rem"><mark style="background-color:rgba(0, 0, 0, 0)" class="has-inline-color has-background-color"><strong>W</strong>ORLD <strong>H</strong>EALTH <strong>O</strong>RGANIZATION 2</mark></h2>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:paragraph {"align":"center","style":{"typography":{"fontSize":"1.2rem"}}} -->
<p class="has-text-align-center" style="font-size:1.2rem"><mark style="background-color:rgba(0, 0, 0, 0);color:#cecbcc" class="has-inline-color"><strong>Agenda</strong>: Reforming the Global Medical Tourism Industry</mark></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:spacer {"height":"153px"} -->
<div style="height:153px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<!-- /wp:spacer --></div></div>
<!-- /wp:cover -->

<!-- wp:heading {"textAlign":"center","lock":{"move":true,"remove":true},"style":{"typography":{"fontSize":"2.4rem"}},"textColor":"vivid-cyan-blue"} -->
<h2 class="wp-block-heading has-text-align-center has-vivid-cyan-blue-color has-text-color" style="font-size:2.4rem"><strong>Letter From The Chairperson</strong></h2>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:group {"align":"wide","layout":{"type":"flex","orientation":"vertical","verticalAlignment":"center","justifyContent":"center"}} -->
<div class="wp-block-group alignwide"><!-- wp:image {"id":4835,"width":265,"height":325,"scale":"cover","sizeSlug":"large","linkDestination":"none"} -->
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large is-resized"><img src="https://shishukunjmun4.files.wordpress.com/2023/07/tanya-1.jpg?w=950" alt="" class="wp-image-4835" style="object-fit:cover;width:265px;height:325px" width="265" height="325" /></figure>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:group {"style":{"layout":{"selfStretch":"fixed","flexSize":"700px"}},"layout":{"type":"flex","orientation":"vertical","verticalAlignment":"top","justifyContent":"left"}} -->
<div class="wp-block-group"><!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Dear Delegates,<br>I, Tanya Dhakad, Chairperson of the World Health Organisation, find pleasure in welcoming you to the Junior Shishukunj Model United Nations 2023.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>I am an eleventh-grader studying Humanities with Applied Math and Entrepreneurship. I have a pronounced interest in poetry, writing and public speaking. I aspire to pursue journalism at Yale, New Haven. The knack for poetry comes from life experiences and the need to write it all down. Ive co-authored 3 books till now. Music is something which intrigues me and Ill be more than elated to find good song recommendations my way. My first MUN was back in the 6th grade and I can proudly say that it shaped over half of my personality. Youll always find me talking so that is your cue to feel free to reach out to me anytime. I love to read and youll often find me digging through conspiracy theories. I firmly stand by Thomas Edisons last words Its very beautiful over there. I dont know where it is, but I believe its somewhere, and I hope its beautiful.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>The agenda of this committee,<strong> Reforming the Global Medical Tourism Industry, </strong>has been set to enable delegates to become better thinkers, debaters, facilitators and all in all become individuals capable of dealing with this crucial issue through focus and wise decision-making.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>For a delegate, quick thinking and following one's instincts are just as important as comprehensive research. With an emphasis on debating skills, creativity, tactical negotiation, etc we hope to give you the best experience at this conference. Feel free to contact our bureau for any doubts/queries or help you may need.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>We wish you the best of luck for the conference.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Regards<br><strong>Tanya Dhakad</strong><br><strong>Chairperson</strong><br><strong>WHO 2</strong></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph --></div>
<!-- /wp:group -->

<!-- wp:separator {"style":{"layout":{"selfStretch":"fixed","flexSize":null}},"className":"is-style-wide"} -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity is-style-wide" />
<!-- /wp:separator --></div>
<!-- /wp:group -->

<!-- wp:separator {"lock":{"move":true,"remove":true},"align":"wide","className":"is-style-wide"} -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator alignwide has-alpha-channel-opacity is-style-wide" />
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:heading {"textAlign":"left","lock":{"move":true,"remove":true},"align":"wide","style":{"typography":{"fontSize":"2.4rem"}},"textColor":"vivid-cyan-blue"} -->
<h2 class="wp-block-heading alignwide has-text-align-left has-vivid-cyan-blue-color has-text-color" style="font-size:2.4rem"><strong>Organ Description</strong></h2>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:group {"align":"wide","layout":{"type":"default"}} -->
<div class="wp-block-group alignwide"><!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>The voice of health within the UN, the World Health Organization is the directing and coordinating authority for public health in the United Nations system. Committed to integrity and excellence in health, the WHO provides leadership on global health matters, shapes the health research agenda, sets norms and standards, articulates evidence-based policy options and monitors and assesses health trends. WHOs work remains firmly rooted in the principles of equity, integrity and inclusion. Collaboration is at the heart of all it does. From governments and civil societies to international organizations, foundations, advocates, researchers and health workers, it mobilizes every part of society to advance the health and security of all. It connects nations, partners and people to promote health, to keep the world safe and serve the vulnerable. The WHO aims to let everyone attain the highest level of health.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:separator {"align":"wide","className":"is-style-wide"} -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator alignwide has-alpha-channel-opacity is-style-wide" />
<!-- /wp:separator --></div>
<!-- /wp:group -->

<!-- wp:heading {"textAlign":"left","lock":{"move":true,"remove":true},"align":"wide","style":{"typography":{"fontSize":"2.4rem"}},"textColor":"vivid-cyan-blue"} -->
<h2 class="wp-block-heading alignwide has-text-align-left has-vivid-cyan-blue-color has-text-color" style="font-size:2.4rem"><strong>Agenda : Reforming the Global Medical Tourism Industry</strong></h2>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:group {"align":"wide","layout":{"type":"default"}} -->
<div class="wp-block-group alignwide"><!-- wp:paragraph {"align":"left"} -->
<p class="has-text-align-left">The World Health Organization (WHO) recognizes the importance of addressing the challenges and issues surrounding the global medical tourism industry. This agenda aims to raise awareness about the complexities associated with medical tourism and the need for reform. Medical tourism is a term used to describe the rapidly growing practice of traveling across international borders to seek healthcare services. Services typically sought by travelers include elective procedures as well as complex surgeries, etc. The medical tourism sector has a lot of potential to grow but is also confronted with many challenges that need to be tackled. The follow-up care is very difficult in the case of medical tourism. One of the serious concerns relates to differences in laws in different countries. There are no uniform laws and moreover, in most countries there are weak laws for malpractice in medical services which leave patients with fewer options to fight for their rights in case they are cheated or if something goes wrong during the whole medical process. Disparities in healthcare access, resources, and infrastructure between different countries contribute to variations in medical tourism trends and raise ethical concerns. The committee aims to form solutions and regulations regarding such concerns.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph --></div>
<!-- /wp:group -->

<!-- wp:separator {"align":"wide","className":"is-style-wide"} -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator alignwide has-alpha-channel-opacity is-style-wide" />
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:columns -->
<div class="wp-block-columns"><!-- wp:column -->
<div class="wp-block-column"><!-- wp:image {"id":1231,"width":279,"height":246,"sizeSlug":"large","linkDestination":"custom"} -->
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large is-resized"><a href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/1G6SPAh4qrG1lxslC6NwkGmUsJ62zn9m4/view?usp=sharing"><img src="https://shishukunjmun4.files.wordpress.com/2023/05/who-emblem-1.png?w=841" alt="" class="wp-image-1231" style="width:279px;height:246px" width="279" height="246" /></a><figcaption class="wp-element-caption"><strong>Study Guide</strong></figcaption></figure>
<!-- /wp:image --></div>
<!-- /wp:column -->

<!-- wp:column -->
<div class="wp-block-column"><!-- wp:image {"id":3032,"width":211,"height":243,"sizeSlug":"large","linkDestination":"custom"} -->
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large is-resized"><a href="https://shishukunjmun4.files.wordpress.com/2023/07/who2.pdf"><img src="https://shishukunjmun4.files.wordpress.com/2023/06/pdf_file_icon.svg_.png?w=640" alt="" class="wp-image-3032" style="width:211px;height:243px" width="211" height="243" /></a><figcaption class="wp-element-caption"><strong>Allotments</strong></figcaption></figure>

<p></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:heading {"textAlign":"center","style":{"typography":{"fontSize":"2.6rem"}}} -->
<h2 class="wp-block-heading has-text-align-center" style="font-size:2.6rem"><mark style="background-color:rgba(0, 0, 0, 0)" class="has-inline-color has-background-color"><strong>W</strong>ORLD <strong>H</strong>EALTH <strong>O</strong>RGANIZATION 1</mark></h2>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:paragraph {"align":"center","style":{"typography":{"fontSize":"1.2rem"}}} -->
<p class="has-text-align-center" style="font-size:1.2rem"><mark style="background-color:rgba(0, 0, 0, 0);color:#cecbcc" class="has-inline-color"><strong>Agenda</strong>: Establishing Preparedness Protocols for Protecting Against Future Pandemics</mark></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:spacer {"height":"153px"} -->
<div style="height:153px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<!-- /wp:spacer --></div></div>
<!-- /wp:cover -->

<!-- wp:heading {"textAlign":"center","lock":{"move":true,"remove":true},"style":{"typography":{"fontSize":"2.4rem"}},"textColor":"vivid-cyan-blue"} -->
<h2 class="wp-block-heading has-text-align-center has-vivid-cyan-blue-color has-text-color" style="font-size:2.4rem"><strong>Letter From The Chairperson</strong></h2>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:group {"align":"wide","layout":{"type":"flex","orientation":"vertical","verticalAlignment":"center","justifyContent":"center"}} -->
<div class="wp-block-group alignwide"><!-- wp:image {"id":4831,"width":265,"height":325,"scale":"cover","sizeSlug":"large","linkDestination":"none"} -->
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large is-resized"><img src="https://shishukunjmun4.files.wordpress.com/2023/07/dsc_0628-2-edited.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-4831" style="object-fit:cover;width:265px;height:325px" width="265" height="325" /></figure>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:group {"style":{"layout":{"selfStretch":"fixed","flexSize":"700px"}},"layout":{"type":"flex","orientation":"vertical","verticalAlignment":"top","justifyContent":"left"}} -->
<div class="wp-block-group"><!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Dear delegates,</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>I am delighted to extend an invitation to all bright young minds to the first ever junior Shishukunj mun. We all aspire that this conference enriches you with new insights on the topic of health and improves your MUN skills.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>A little myself, Suhan Jain will be serving as your chairperson for WHO-1. Im in eleventh grade studying PCB with psychology. I aspire to become a scientist in the field of microbiology and that's why I love this agenda so much. During my leisure time I also get involved in activities like playing guitar, I cherish music like nothing else (a Swiftie, to be specific).</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>&nbsp;When it comes to sports I love obliterating others at the basketball court. Playing sports has also helped me to inculcate abilities like sportsman spirit and has enabled me to learn from both failures and successes. I have taken part in numerous MUNs but I still remember how frightened I was in my first MUN. Well, I assure you that Ill be there for all of you throughout this whole journey and I have a lot to learn from you guys. Looking forward to meeting my lovely juniors and seeing the faces of young intellectuals who will carry the Shishukunj legacy forward.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>We acknowledge the fact that participation in a MUN demands a significant amount of dedication and time but rest assured this will be an experience unlike any before, so pull up your socks and get ready for an adventure.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>The agenda of our committee is Establishing Preparedness Protocols for Protecting Against Future Pandemics. Our focal point is primarily directed towards the Monkeypox virus, which has emerged as a pressing concern. It has been spreading across various regions worldwide.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>We look forward to your participation and hope that there will be constructive and intelligent discussions. I believe that you will give each other strong yet healthy competition.<br><br>In case of any queries, kindly feel free to contact the bureau through the school mail or group.<br><br>Regards&nbsp;<br><strong>Suhan Jain</strong><br><strong>Chairperson</strong><br><strong>WHO 1</strong></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph --></div>
<!-- /wp:group -->

<!-- wp:separator {"style":{"layout":{"selfStretch":"fixed","flexSize":null}},"className":"is-style-wide"} -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity is-style-wide" />
<!-- /wp:separator --></div>
<!-- /wp:group -->

<!-- wp:separator {"lock":{"move":true,"remove":true},"align":"wide","className":"is-style-wide"} -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator alignwide has-alpha-channel-opacity is-style-wide" />
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:heading {"textAlign":"left","lock":{"move":true,"remove":true},"align":"wide","style":{"typography":{"fontSize":"2.4rem"}},"textColor":"vivid-cyan-blue"} -->
<h2 class="wp-block-heading alignwide has-text-align-left has-vivid-cyan-blue-color has-text-color" style="font-size:2.4rem"><strong>Organ Description</strong></h2>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:group {"align":"wide","layout":{"type":"default"}} -->
<div class="wp-block-group alignwide"><!-- wp:paragraph {"align":"left"} -->
<p class="has-text-align-left">The World Health Organization is acknowledged as the leading voice of the United Nations on public health matters, responsible for directing and coordinating international health efforts. Its mission is to uphold the highest standards of health integrity and excellence, overseeing global health affairs, establishing health norms and standards, influencing research agendas, developing evidence-based policies, and monitoring health trends. By partnering with countries, organizations, and people, the WHO endeavors to enhance health promotion, ensure worldwide safety, and support disadvantaged communities, with the ultimate aim of facilitating universal access to optimal health.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:separator {"align":"wide","className":"is-style-wide"} -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator alignwide has-alpha-channel-opacity is-style-wide" />
<!-- /wp:separator --></div>
<!-- /wp:group -->

<!-- wp:heading {"textAlign":"left","lock":{"move":true,"remove":true},"align":"wide","style":{"typography":{"fontSize":"2.4rem"}},"textColor":"vivid-cyan-blue"} -->
<h2 class="wp-block-heading alignwide has-text-align-left has-vivid-cyan-blue-color has-text-color" style="font-size:2.4rem"><strong>Agenda : Establishing Preparedness Protocols for Protecting Against Future Pandemics</strong></h2>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:group {"align":"wide","layout":{"type":"default"}} -->
<div class="wp-block-group alignwide"><!-- wp:paragraph {"align":"left"} -->
<p class="has-text-align-left">People are the greatest treasure of a country. These were some true words said by Nelson Mandela, the first black President of South Africa. Have you ever contemplated the scenario of a country devoid of its populace? Certainly not. However, when the individuals within a nation suffer from poor health and lack protection against pandemics, the question arises: Can a country effectively operate? Once again, the answer unequivocally remains a resounding "NO." Health is not a question of income but its a fundamental right, and this is what our agenda emphasizes on. We all have recently faced a global pandemic lasting for almost two years and time and time again this would be our greatest concern, to prevent the world from any future pandemics. Due to the recent rise of cases of Monkeypox virus, we shall take appropriate measures so as to avoid a lockdown and prevent bringing the economy back down after its recent recovery. The ultimate goal of our committee is to put forward effective solutions that are not just suggestions, but will rather help us fight this issue at a global level, thus, making it an agenda to be discussed as quickly as possible before the virus spreads like wildfire.&nbsp;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph --></div>
<!-- /wp:group -->

<!-- wp:separator {"align":"wide","className":"is-style-wide"} -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator alignwide has-alpha-channel-opacity is-style-wide" />
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:columns -->
<div class="wp-block-columns"><!-- wp:column -->
<div class="wp-block-column"><!-- wp:image {"id":1203,"width":277,"height":245,"sizeSlug":"large","linkDestination":"custom"} -->
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large is-resized"><a href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/11WjLU5jfEpEwByVzR_nQ4U25X0LEqKrA/view?usp=sharing"><img src="https://shishukunjmun4.files.wordpress.com/2023/05/who-emblem.png?w=841" alt="" class="wp-image-1203" style="width:277px;height:245px" width="277" height="245" /></a><figcaption class="wp-element-caption"><strong>Study Guide</strong></figcaption></figure>
<!-- /wp:image --></div>
<!-- /wp:column -->

<!-- wp:column -->
<div class="wp-block-column"><!-- wp:image {"id":3032,"width":211,"height":243,"sizeSlug":"large","linkDestination":"custom"} -->

  <description/>
  <content:encoded><![CDATA[<!-- wp:cover {"url":"https://shishukunjmun4.files.wordpress.com/2023/06/stock-vector-world-day-against-child-labour-may-day-concept-art-2194555925-transformed.jpeg","id":2146,"dimRatio":50,"minHeight":680,"contentPosition":"center center","align":"full","style":{"spacing":{"padding":{"right":"var:preset|spacing|60","left":"var:preset|spacing|60"}}},"layout":{"type":"default"}} -->
<div class="wp-block-cover alignfull" style="padding-right:var(--wp--preset--spacing--60);padding-left:var(--wp--preset--spacing--60);min-height:680px"><span aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-cover__background has-background-dim"></span><img class="wp-block-cover__image-background wp-image-2146" alt="" src="https://shishukunjmun4.files.wordpress.com/2023/06/stock-vector-world-day-against-child-labour-may-day-concept-art-2194555925-transformed.jpeg" data-object-fit="cover" /><div class="wp-block-cover__inner-container"><!-- wp:columns -->
<div class="wp-block-columns"><!-- wp:column {"verticalAlignment":"center"} -->
<div class="wp-block-column is-vertically-aligned-center"><!-- wp:group {"layout":{"type":"flex"}} -->
<div class="wp-block-group"><!-- wp:site-logo {"width":166} /--></div>
<!-- /wp:group --></div>
<!-- /wp:column -->

<!-- wp:column {"verticalAlignment":"center","width":"1054px"} -->
<div class="wp-block-column is-vertically-aligned-center" style="flex-basis:1054px"><!-- wp:group {"layout":{"type":"flex","flexWrap":"nowrap","justifyContent":"right"}} -->
<div class="wp-block-group"><!-- wp:navigation {"ref":1011,"textColor":"background","showSubmenuIcon":false,"icon":"menu","layout":{"type":"flex","justifyContent":"right","orientation":"horizontal","flexWrap":"wrap"},"style":{"layout":{"selfStretch":"fill","flexSize":null},"spacing":{"blockGap":"var:preset|spacing|50"},"typography":{"fontSize":"1rem"}}} /--></div>
<!-- /wp:group --></div>
<!-- /wp:column --></div>
<!-- /wp:columns -->

<!-- wp:spacer {"height":"53px"} -->
<div style="height:53px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<!-- /wp:spacer -->

<!-- wp:heading {"textAlign":"center","style":{"typography":{"fontSize":"2.6rem"}}} -->
<h2 class="wp-block-heading has-text-align-center" style="font-size:2.6rem"><mark style="background-color:rgba(0, 0, 0, 0)" class="has-inline-color has-background-color"><strong>U</strong>NITED <strong>N</strong>ATION'S <strong>C</strong>HILDREN'S <strong>F</strong>UND 1</mark></h2>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:paragraph {"align":"center","style":{"typography":{"fontSize":"1.2rem"}}} -->
<p class="has-text-align-center" style="font-size:1.2rem"><mark style="background-color:rgba(0, 0, 0, 0);color:#cecbcc" class="has-inline-color"><strong>Agenda</strong>: Upholding Child Rights and Combating Child Labour</mark></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:spacer {"height":"153px"} -->
<div style="height:153px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<!-- /wp:spacer --></div></div>
<!-- /wp:cover -->

<!-- wp:heading {"textAlign":"center","lock":{"move":true,"remove":true},"style":{"typography":{"fontSize":"2.4rem"}},"textColor":"vivid-cyan-blue"} -->
<h2 class="wp-block-heading has-text-align-center has-vivid-cyan-blue-color has-text-color" style="font-size:2.4rem"><strong>Letter From The Chairperson</strong></h2>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:group {"align":"wide","layout":{"type":"flex","orientation":"vertical","verticalAlignment":"center","justifyContent":"center"}} -->
<div class="wp-block-group alignwide"><!-- wp:image {"id":4816,"width":265,"height":325,"scale":"cover","sizeSlug":"large","linkDestination":"none"} -->
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large is-resized"><img src="https://shishukunjmun4.files.wordpress.com/2023/07/parth-1.jpg?w=851" alt="" class="wp-image-4816" style="object-fit:cover;width:265px;height:325px" width="265" height="325" /></figure>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:group {"style":{"layout":{"selfStretch":"fixed","flexSize":"700px"}},"layout":{"type":"flex","orientation":"vertical","verticalAlignment":"top","justifyContent":"left"}} -->
<div class="wp-block-group"><!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Dear Delegates,<br>With utmost pleasure, I am privileged to welcome you all to the Shishukunj MUN - Junior Edition 2023. I am Parth Badlani and I am honored to be serving as the chairperson for the United Nations International Childrens Emergency Fund (UNICEF-1).</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>I am a tenth grader who wishes to pursue Culinary Arts at Le Cordon Bleu in Melbourne, Australia. I am an extrovert who loves to socialize and meet new people every day and a person who is approachable and always open to any kind of talk at all times. I am thrilled to be serving in this role, combining my passion for baking with the spirit of debating and diplomacy, so you might be ready for some treats coming your way. I have attended over 11 MUNs and remember how I started MUNing as a hesitant sixth grader and never thought of serving as a chairperson today. I am often full of excitement and curiosity, and I promise to transform a nervous you into a confident and fearless beginner. I also like to create social media content, so you might see me scrolling through reels if not baking. I also believe that there is not a single day where you dont learn something, keep learning and live every day like its your last. Problems come your way at the smallest of times, dont keep crying about what the problem is, rather look for the solution, analyze critically and let your brain innovate ideas to its fullest.&nbsp;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Thats what Model United Nations is all about, its about research, confidence, and collaboration. With the knowledge gained from the study guide and your independent research, you will be able to come up with a wide range of innovative ideas. And through collaboration, ideas from you and others will form a realistic solution. I am always here to guide and assist you at all times and urge you to actively engage in fruitful debates, solve all upcoming challenges and just be YOU, be who you are and let your inner self glow.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Eagerly look forward to seeing you all and I hope this conference is fun, engaging and a successful one!</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p><br>Regards<br><strong><strong>Parth Badlani</strong><br><strong>Chairperson</strong></strong><br><strong>UNICEF 1</strong></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph --></div>
<!-- /wp:group -->

<!-- wp:separator {"style":{"layout":{"selfStretch":"fixed","flexSize":null}},"className":"is-style-wide"} -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity is-style-wide" />
<!-- /wp:separator --></div>
<!-- /wp:group -->

<!-- wp:separator {"lock":{"move":true,"remove":true},"align":"wide","className":"is-style-wide"} -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator alignwide has-alpha-channel-opacity is-style-wide" />
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:heading {"textAlign":"left","lock":{"move":true,"remove":true},"align":"wide","style":{"typography":{"fontSize":"2.4rem"}},"textColor":"vivid-cyan-blue"} -->
<h2 class="wp-block-heading alignwide has-text-align-left has-vivid-cyan-blue-color has-text-color" style="font-size:2.4rem"><strong>Organ Description</strong></h2>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:group {"align":"wide","layout":{"type":"default"}} -->
<div class="wp-block-group alignwide"><!-- wp:paragraph {"align":"left"} -->
<p class="has-text-align-left">The United Nations Childrens Fund (UNICEF) was created in 1946. It is a humanitarian and development agency that works towards defending rights for every child around the globe. These rights include having safe shelter, protection, education, nutrition, clean water, and health care. UNICEF has a global presence and collaborates with leaders and policy makers to help all children, especially those who are disadvantaged. UNICEF operates in more than 190 countries, working closely with governments, non-governmental organizations (NGOs), and other partners to address the needs of children and their rights. UNICEFs main aim is to drive change for children and young people every day, across the globe. UNICEF believes that every child has the right to grow up in a safe and inclusive environment. It also works with partners around the world to promote policies and expand access to services that protect all children. Overall, UNICEF plays a crucial role in advocating for children's rights, providing assistance, and working towards a world where every child can survive and thrive.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:separator {"align":"wide","className":"is-style-wide"} -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator alignwide has-alpha-channel-opacity is-style-wide" />
<!-- /wp:separator --></div>
<!-- /wp:group -->

<!-- wp:heading {"textAlign":"left","lock":{"move":true,"remove":true},"align":"wide","style":{"typography":{"fontSize":"2.4rem"}},"textColor":"vivid-cyan-blue"} -->
<h2 class="wp-block-heading alignwide has-text-align-left has-vivid-cyan-blue-color has-text-color" style="font-size:2.4rem"><strong>Agenda : Upholding Child Rights and Combating Child Labour</strong></h2>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:group {"align":"wide","layout":{"type":"default"}} -->
<div class="wp-block-group alignwide"><!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>The most defenseless and priceless members of society are children. They are entitled to fundamental human rights like the right to an unharmed childhood and the right to healthcare, education, and safety from violence.&nbsp;Any work that robs children of their youth, hinders their education, or is hazardous to their bodily or mental health is referred to as child labor. It encompasses both dangerous and non-hazardous activities, such as farming as well as working in mines. Governments, civil society organizations, and the commercial sector must work together to protect children's rights and end child labour. It involves creating and implementing policies and plans to protect children from exploitation, ensure their access to essential needs such as healthcare, education, and food, and raise awareness. Thus, it is imperative that everyone work together to end child labour and make sure that every child has the chance to realize their full potential.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph --></div>
<!-- /wp:group -->

<!-- wp:separator {"align":"wide","className":"is-style-wide"} -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator alignwide has-alpha-channel-opacity is-style-wide" />
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:columns -->
<div class="wp-block-columns"><!-- wp:column -->
<div class="wp-block-column"><!-- wp:image {"id":1211,"width":341,"height":191,"sizeSlug":"large","linkDestination":"custom"} -->
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large is-resized"><a href="https://shishukunjmun4.files.wordpress.com/2023/07/study-guide-unicef-merged.pdf"><img src="https://shishukunjmun4.files.wordpress.com/2023/05/unicef-logo-1.png?w=1024" alt="" class="wp-image-1211" style="width:341px;height:191px" width="341" height="191" /></a><figcaption class="wp-element-caption"><strong>Study Guide</strong></figcaption></figure>
<!-- /wp:image --></div>
<!-- /wp:column -->

<!-- wp:column -->
<div class="wp-block-column"><!-- wp:image {"id":3032,"width":168,"height":194,"sizeSlug":"large","linkDestination":"custom"} -->
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large is-resized"><a href="https://shishukunjmun4.files.wordpress.com/2023/07/uncf.pdf"><img src="https://shishukunjmun4.files.wordpress.com/2023/06/pdf_file_icon.svg_.png?w=640" alt="" class="wp-image-3032" style="width:168px;height:194px" width="168" height="194" /></a><figcaption class="wp-element-caption"><strong>Allotments</strong></figcaption></figure>

<div class="wp-block-column is-vertically-aligned-center" style="flex-basis:1054px"><!-- wp:group {"layout":{"type":"flex","flexWrap":"nowrap","justifyContent":"right"}} -->
<div class="wp-block-group"><!-- wp:navigation {"ref":1011,"textColor":"background","showSubmenuIcon":false,"icon":"menu","layout":{"type":"flex","justifyContent":"right","orientation":"horizontal","flexWrap":"wrap"},"style":{"layout":{"selfStretch":"fill","flexSize":null},"spacing":{"blockGap":"var:preset|spacing|50"},"typography":{"fontSize":"1rem"}}} /--></div>

<!-- wp:heading {"textAlign":"center","style":{"typography":{"fontSize":"2.6rem"}}} -->
<h2 class="wp-block-heading has-text-align-center" style="font-size:2.6rem"><mark style="background-color:rgba(0, 0, 0, 0)" class="has-inline-color has-background-color"><strong>U</strong>NITED <strong>N</strong>ATION'S <strong>C</strong>HILDREN'S <strong>F</strong>UND 2</mark></h2>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:paragraph {"align":"center","style":{"typography":{"fontSize":"1.2rem"}}} -->
<p class="has-text-align-center" style="font-size:1.2rem"><mark style="background-color:rgba(0, 0, 0, 0);color:#cecbcc" class="has-inline-color"><strong><mark style="background-color:rgba(0, 0, 0, 0);color:#cecbcc" class="has-inline-color"><strong>Agenda</strong></mark></strong>: Addressing Challenges Faced by War Affected Children Worldwide</mark></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:spacer {"height":"153px"} -->
<div style="height:153px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<!-- /wp:spacer --></div></div>
<!-- /wp:cover -->

<!-- wp:heading {"textAlign":"center","lock":{"move":true,"remove":true},"style":{"typography":{"fontSize":"2.4rem"}},"textColor":"vivid-cyan-blue"} -->
<h2 class="wp-block-heading has-text-align-center has-vivid-cyan-blue-color has-text-color" style="font-size:2.4rem"><strong>Letter From The Chairperson</strong></h2>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:group {"align":"wide","layout":{"type":"flex","orientation":"vertical","verticalAlignment":"center","justifyContent":"center"}} -->
<div class="wp-block-group alignwide"><!-- wp:image {"id":4436,"width":513,"height":341,"sizeSlug":"large","linkDestination":"none"} -->
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large is-resized"><img src="https://shishukunjmun4.files.wordpress.com/2023/07/60a8584-1-edited-6.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-4436" style="width:513px;height:341px" width="513" height="341" /></figure>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:group {"style":{"layout":{"selfStretch":"fixed","flexSize":"700px"}},"layout":{"type":"flex","orientation":"vertical","verticalAlignment":"top","justifyContent":"left"}} -->
<div class="wp-block-group"><!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Dear Delegates,<br>We, Dhiya Khandelwal and Mithran Ladhania, feel immense pleasure in welcoming you all to the Junior Shishukunj MUN 2023. We are honored to be assuming the roles of co-chairpersons for the United Nations Childrens Fund - 2.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p> I, Dhiya Khandelwal, am a twelfth-grader and will be serving as the co-chairperson of UNICEF-2. I love to explore the adventure, nature presents before us and find my inspiration through music and art. I like to steal time from studying physics, chemistry, and mathematics to craft delicious dishes from around the world. I have been MUNing since the seventh grade and it has led me to explore some of the best parts of me. I hope this and all the upcoming MUNs you participate in do the same for you.&nbsp;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>I, Mithran Ladhania, am a tenth-grader, and I will serve as the co-chairperson of this committee, UNICEF2. I am a reader and a Star Wars fan at heart, and whenever Im not idling at my desk or playing tennis, I can be found with a good book or a Playstation controller in my hand. I attended my first MUN in eighth grade, and I have been MUNing ever since. You can always feel confident in approaching me or Dhiya with any query you have (even if it's Star Wars related)</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>UNICEF is committed to being the voice of children worldwide. The agenda for this year is Addressing Challenges Faced by War-Affected Children Worldwide. In todays world, not a day goes by when hundreds of innocent children worldwide, from Yemen to Ukraine to Syria and beyond, do not face the side effects of an all-out war. This committee aims to discuss the same and try to come up with solutions that address both the long-term and short-term needs of these children. We are committed to making this MUN a memorable experience for everyone. We look forward to meeting you all soon.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>The Shishukunj MUN - Junior Edition will be having ten dynamic committees each with a fascinating agenda pertinent not only to the present but also to historical conflicts and futuristic regulations. Beyond the skills of debate and negotiation that the delegates will practice over the course of the conference, it is vital to realize that vision and ambition are equally as important.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Delegates and faculty advisors, it is an honor to serve as your Secretary-General. Our team cannot wait to hear your ideas and witness your intellectual curiosity. The entire Secretariat and Bureau are determined in ensuring a worthwhile experience for every student and making this MUN one of their most memorable experiences. Hoping to see you at the conference!</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Regards<br><strong>Mithran Ladhania &amp; Dhiya Khandelwal</strong><br><strong>Co-Chairpersons</strong><br><strong>UNICEF 2</strong></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph --></div>
<!-- /wp:group -->

<!-- wp:paragraph {"lock":{"move":true,"remove":true}} -->
<p></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:separator {"style":{"layout":{"selfStretch":"fixed","flexSize":null}},"className":"is-style-wide"} -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity is-style-wide" />
<!-- /wp:separator --></div>
<!-- /wp:group -->

<!-- wp:separator {"lock":{"move":true,"remove":true},"align":"wide","className":"is-style-wide"} -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator alignwide has-alpha-channel-opacity is-style-wide" />
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:heading {"textAlign":"left","lock":{"move":true,"remove":true},"align":"wide","style":{"typography":{"fontSize":"2.4rem"}},"textColor":"vivid-cyan-blue"} -->
<h2 class="wp-block-heading alignwide has-text-align-left has-vivid-cyan-blue-color has-text-color" style="font-size:2.4rem"><strong>Organ Description</strong></h2>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:group {"align":"wide","layout":{"type":"default"}} -->
<div class="wp-block-group alignwide"><!-- wp:paragraph {"align":"left"} -->
<p class="has-text-align-left">Since 1946, the United Nations Childrens Fund has been committed to addressing the needs of every child: the citizens of tomorrows world. Considering itself to be the spokesperson for the thousands of children who cannot speak for themselves today, UNICEF looks past the veil of complex world politics, ensuring that grim problems today do not prevent any child from reaching their true potential. UNICEF has not just limited itself to just making resolutions rather it is present on the ground with children dealing with diverse issues, from disability to war. UNICEF hopes to create a better world for the lives of the children today.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:separator {"align":"wide","className":"is-style-wide"} -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator alignwide has-alpha-channel-opacity is-style-wide" />
<!-- /wp:separator --></div>
<!-- /wp:group -->

<!-- wp:heading {"textAlign":"left","lock":{"move":true,"remove":true},"align":"wide","style":{"typography":{"fontSize":"2.4rem"}},"textColor":"vivid-cyan-blue"} -->
<h2 class="wp-block-heading alignwide has-text-align-left has-vivid-cyan-blue-color has-text-color" style="font-size:2.4rem"><strong>Agenda : Addressing Challenges Faced by War Affected Children Worldwide</strong></h2>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:group {"align":"wide","layout":{"type":"default"}} -->
<div class="wp-block-group alignwide"><!-- wp:paragraph {"align":"left"} -->
<p class="has-text-align-left">The international scene today is dotted with numerous wars. From the civil wars in the Middle East to the Russia-Ukraine war, to the militant revolutions in Africa. The greatest scars of war are left on the third party of the war: the countrys people. Among these, possibly the worst affected are the children. One day, they may be going to school, living normal lives, and the next day, theyre sent across borders to refugee camps, with their entire life left hanging. Living lives that are scarce of food, lack education, or a proper place to live. But, the most crucial thing stolen from children living in war-ridden countries is their sense of safety and security. With international wars occurring at an even higher rate, the echoes of this issue are beginning to sound in all corners of the world.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph --></div>
<!-- /wp:group -->

<!-- wp:separator {"align":"wide","className":"is-style-wide"} -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator alignwide has-alpha-channel-opacity is-style-wide" />
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:columns -->
<div class="wp-block-columns"><!-- wp:column -->
<div class="wp-block-column"><!-- wp:image {"id":1208,"width":250,"height":140,"sizeSlug":"large","linkDestination":"custom"} -->
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large is-resized"><a href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/15bAtMSc7EfgadprlQ2WuW8Lkc6ocKj9Y/view?usp=sharing"><img src="https://shishukunjmun4.files.wordpress.com/2023/05/unicef-logo.png?w=1024" alt="" class="wp-image-1208" style="width:250px;height:140px" width="250" height="140" /></a><figcaption class="wp-element-caption"><strong>Study Guide</strong></figcaption></figure>
<!-- /wp:image --></div>
<!-- /wp:column -->

<!-- wp:column -->
<div class="wp-block-column"><!-- wp:image {"id":3032,"width":120,"height":138,"sizeSlug":"large","linkDestination":"custom"} -->
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large is-resized"><a href="https://shishukunjmun4.files.wordpress.com/2023/07/uncf2.pdf"><img src="https://shishukunjmun4.files.wordpress.com/2023/06/pdf_file_icon.svg_.png?w=640" alt="" class="wp-image-3032" style="width:120px;height:138px" width="120" height="138" /></a><figcaption class="wp-element-caption"><strong>Allotments</strong></figcaption></figure>

  <description/>

<div class="wp-block-cover alignfull is-light" style="padding-right:var(--wp--preset--spacing--60);padding-left:var(--wp--preset--spacing--60);min-height:680px"><span aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-cover__background has-background-dim"></span><img class="wp-block-cover__image-background wp-image-1197" alt="" src="https://shishukunjmun4.files.wordpress.com/2023/05/screenshot-2023-05-11-233926-1.png" data-object-fit="cover" /><div class="wp-block-cover__inner-container"><!-- wp:columns -->
<div class="wp-block-columns"><!-- wp:column {"verticalAlignment":"center"} -->
<div class="wp-block-column is-vertically-aligned-center"><!-- wp:group {"layout":{"type":"flex"}} -->
<div class="wp-block-group"><!-- wp:site-logo {"width":166} /--></div>
<!-- /wp:group --></div>
<!-- /wp:column -->

<!-- wp:column {"verticalAlignment":"center","width":"1054px"} -->
<div class="wp-block-column is-vertically-aligned-center" style="flex-basis:1054px"><!-- wp:group {"layout":{"type":"flex","flexWrap":"nowrap","justifyContent":"right"}} -->
<div class="wp-block-group"><!-- wp:navigation {"ref":1011,"textColor":"background","showSubmenuIcon":false,"icon":"menu","layout":{"type":"flex","justifyContent":"right","orientation":"horizontal","flexWrap":"wrap"},"style":{"layout":{"selfStretch":"fill","flexSize":null},"spacing":{"blockGap":"var:preset|spacing|50"},"typography":{"fontSize":"1rem"}}} /--></div>
<!-- /wp:group --></div>
<!-- /wp:column --></div>
<!-- /wp:columns -->

<!-- wp:spacer {"height":"53px"} -->
<div style="height:53px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<!-- /wp:spacer -->

<!-- wp:heading {"textAlign":"center","style":{"typography":{"fontSize":"2.6rem"}}} -->
<h2 class="wp-block-heading has-text-align-center" style="font-size:2.6rem"><mark style="background-color:rgba(0, 0, 0, 0)" class="has-inline-color has-background-color"><strong>U</strong>NITED <strong>N</strong>ATIONS <strong>E</strong>DUCATIONAL,<strong>S</strong>CIENTIFIC <strong>A</strong>ND <strong>C</strong>ULTURAL <strong>O</strong>RGANIZATION 1</mark></h2>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:paragraph {"align":"center","style":{"typography":{"fontSize":"1.2rem"}}} -->
<p class="has-text-align-center" style="font-size:1.2rem"><mark style="background-color:rgba(0, 0, 0, 0);color:#cecbcc" class="has-inline-color"><strong>Agenda</strong>: Protecting and Maintaining Cultural Heritage</mark></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:spacer {"height":"153px"} -->
<div style="height:153px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<!-- /wp:spacer --></div></div>
<!-- /wp:cover -->

<!-- wp:heading {"textAlign":"center","lock":{"move":true,"remove":true},"style":{"typography":{"fontSize":"2.4rem"}},"textColor":"vivid-cyan-blue"} -->
<h2 class="wp-block-heading has-text-align-center has-vivid-cyan-blue-color has-text-color" style="font-size:2.4rem"><strong>Letter From The Chairperson</strong></h2>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:group {"align":"wide","layout":{"type":"flex","orientation":"vertical","verticalAlignment":"center","justifyContent":"center"}} -->
<div class="wp-block-group alignwide"><!-- wp:image {"id":4795,"width":265,"height":325,"scale":"cover","sizeSlug":"large","linkDestination":"none"} -->
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large is-resized"><img src="https://shishukunjmun4.files.wordpress.com/2023/07/bi22317-3.jpg?w=886" alt="" class="wp-image-4795" style="object-fit:cover;width:265px;height:325px" width="265" height="325" /></figure>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:group {"style":{"layout":{"selfStretch":"fixed","flexSize":"700px"}},"layout":{"type":"flex","orientation":"vertical","verticalAlignment":"top","justifyContent":"left"}} -->
<div class="wp-block-group"><!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Dear Delegates,<br>It gives me great pleasure to welcome you to the very first edition of The Shishukunj MUN (Junior Edition). I am Harsh Satish, and Im honoured to serve as the Chairperson of The United Nations Educational, Scientific and Cultural Organization 1.&nbsp;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Im currently a Commerce with Applied Mathematics and Entrepreneurship student in 12th grade. I am an exuberant and confident soul who is ever ready to learn and experience new things. Some of my interests include public speaking, writing, international relations, music and sports.&nbsp;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>I have been participating in MUN conferences since when I was in 8th grade, and I believe MUNs are the perfect platform to develop a plethora of invaluable skills that will stay with you all your life. MUNs teach you communication, diplomacy, negotiation, and public speaking and grant you the most valuable asset of all, knowledge. I have gained a great deal from these splendid conferences, and theyve helped me develop myself into the person I am today, and I will do my best to ensure that all of you return from this conference with great memories and invaluable skills.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>The agenda for UNESCO 1 for this conference is Protecting and Maintaining Cultural Heritage, wherein well discuss and debate extensively on ways to protect the indispensable asset we have in cultural heritage and come up with unique solutions for the same.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Feel free to contact me in case of any queries, Ill be happy to be of service.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Looking forward to meeting all of you!</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Regards<br><strong>Harsh Satish</strong><br><strong>Chairperson</strong><br><strong>UNESCO 1</strong></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph --></div>
<!-- /wp:group -->

<!-- wp:separator {"style":{"layout":{"selfStretch":"fixed","flexSize":null}},"className":"is-style-wide"} -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity is-style-wide" />
<!-- /wp:separator --></div>
<!-- /wp:group -->

<!-- wp:separator {"lock":{"move":true,"remove":true},"align":"wide","className":"is-style-wide"} -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator alignwide has-alpha-channel-opacity is-style-wide" />
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:heading {"textAlign":"left","lock":{"move":true,"remove":true},"align":"wide","style":{"typography":{"fontSize":"2.4rem"}},"textColor":"vivid-cyan-blue"} -->
<h2 class="wp-block-heading alignwide has-text-align-left has-vivid-cyan-blue-color has-text-color" style="font-size:2.4rem"><strong>Organ Description</strong></h2>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:group {"align":"wide","layout":{"type":"default"}} -->
<div class="wp-block-group alignwide"><!-- wp:paragraph {"align":"left"} -->
<p class="has-text-align-left">UNESCO, or the United Nations Educational, Scientific and Cultural Organization, stands as a guiding light of global collaboration, UNESCO stands as a pillar of global collaboration, upholding education, science, culture, and communication. It was established in 1945 with the aim of promoting international collaboration in the fields of education, science, culture, and communication. With a determined spirit, it empowers individuals, celebrates diversity, and promotes unity, forging a world where knowledge flourishes, cultures thrive, and humanity unites in shared progress.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:separator {"align":"wide","className":"is-style-wide"} -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator alignwide has-alpha-channel-opacity is-style-wide" />
<!-- /wp:separator --></div>
<!-- /wp:group -->

<!-- wp:heading {"textAlign":"left","lock":{"move":true,"remove":true},"align":"wide","style":{"typography":{"fontSize":"2.4rem"}},"textColor":"vivid-cyan-blue"} -->
<h2 class="wp-block-heading alignwide has-text-align-left has-vivid-cyan-blue-color has-text-color" style="font-size:2.4rem"><strong>Agenda : Protecting and Maintaining Cultural Heritage</strong></h2>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:group {"align":"wide","layout":{"type":"default"}} -->
<div class="wp-block-group alignwide"><!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>As a source of identity, heritage is a valuable factor for empowering local communities and enabling vulnerable groups to participate fully in social and cultural life. Cultural Heritage includes artifacts, monuments, historical sites, traditions, practices, languages and many more that have some symbolic and historic significance. This includes both tangible and intangible cultural heritage. </p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>But, heritage, as valuable as it is, isnt as safe and respected as it should be. Cultural heritage is exposed to many potential risks that endanger its existence. These include war, terrorism, irresponsible tourism, looting and pillage, natural effects such as earthquakes and acid rain. This committee aims to discuss in detail, the cultural heritage and these potential risks, and to come up with sustainable solutions to protect this invaluable asset.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph --></div>
<!-- /wp:group -->

<!-- wp:separator {"align":"wide","className":"is-style-wide"} -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator alignwide has-alpha-channel-opacity is-style-wide" />
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:columns -->
<div class="wp-block-columns"><!-- wp:column -->
<div class="wp-block-column"><!-- wp:image {"id":1201,"width":213,"height":161,"sizeSlug":"large","linkDestination":"custom"} -->
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large is-resized"><a href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/1yYsbwPbY_VFBGA7xmKc5E_0tIsbilB0h/view?usp=sharing"><img src="https://shishukunjmun4.files.wordpress.com/2023/05/d890a-unesco-logo.webp?w=1024" alt="" class="wp-image-1201" style="width:213px;height:161px" width="213" height="161" /></a><figcaption class="wp-element-caption"><strong>Study Guide</strong></figcaption></figure>
<!-- /wp:image --></div>
<!-- /wp:column -->

<!-- wp:column -->
<div class="wp-block-column"><!-- wp:image {"id":3032,"width":138,"height":159,"sizeSlug":"large","linkDestination":"custom"} -->
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large is-resized"><a href="https://shishukunjmun4.files.wordpress.com/2023/07/unesco1.pdf"><img src="https://shishukunjmun4.files.wordpress.com/2023/06/pdf_file_icon.svg_.png?w=640" alt="" class="wp-image-3032" style="width:138px;height:159px" width="138" height="159" /></a><figcaption class="wp-element-caption"><strong>Allotments</strong></figcaption></figure>

<!-- wp:heading {"textAlign":"center","level":1,"style":{"spacing":{"padding":{"top":"0","right":"0","bottom":"0","left":"0"}},"typography":{"fontStyle":"normal","fontWeight":"700","textTransform":"uppercase","fontSize":"3.5rem"},"color":{"text":"#65a7f8"}}} -->
<h1 class="wp-block-heading has-text-align-center has-text-color" style="color:#65a7f8;padding-top:0;padding-right:0;padding-bottom:0;padding-left:0;font-size:3.5rem;font-style:normal;font-weight:700;text-transform:uppercase"><strong>SHISHUKUNJ MUN</strong> 2023</h1>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:heading {"textAlign":"center","style":{"typography":{"textTransform":"uppercase","fontStyle":"normal","fontWeight":"600"}},"textColor":"cyan-bluish-gray","fontSize":"medium"} -->
<h2 class="wp-block-heading has-text-align-center has-cyan-bluish-gray-color has-text-color has-medium-font-size" style="font-style:normal;font-weight:600;text-transform:uppercase"><strong>Jhalaria </strong>senior</h2>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:paragraph {"align":"center","style":{"spacing":{"padding":{"top":"0","right":"0","bottom":"0","left":"0"},"margin":{"top":"0","right":"0","bottom":"0","left":"0"}},"typography":{"fontSize":"2rem"},"color":{"text":"#65a7f8"}}} -->
<p class="has-text-align-center has-text-color" style="color:#65a7f8;margin-top:0;margin-right:0;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;padding-top:0;padding-right:0;padding-bottom:0;padding-left:0;font-size:2rem"><strong>E</strong>merge <strong>E</strong>volve <strong>E</strong>levate</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:spacer {"height":"204px"} -->
<div style="height:204px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<!-- /wp:spacer --></div></div>
<!-- /wp:cover -->

<!-- wp:spacer {"height":"20px"} -->
<div style="height:20px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<!-- /wp:spacer -->

<!-- wp:group {"align":"full","layout":{"type":"flex","flexWrap":"wrap","verticalAlignment":"top","justifyContent":"center"}} -->
<div class="wp-block-group alignfull"><!-- wp:image {"id":3853,"width":210,"height":300,"scale":"cover","sizeSlug":"large","linkDestination":"none"} -->
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large is-resized"><img src="https://shishukunjmun4.files.wordpress.com/2023/07/nishka-kankaria-1-edited.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-3853" style="object-fit:cover;width:210px;height:300px" width="210" height="300" /></figure>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:group {"style":{"layout":{"selfStretch":"fixed","flexSize":"700px"}},"layout":{"type":"flex","orientation":"vertical","verticalAlignment":"top","justifyContent":"left"}} -->
<div class="wp-block-group"><!-- wp:heading {"textAlign":"right","style":{"color":{"text":"#076be3"}}} -->
<h2 class="wp-block-heading has-text-align-right has-text-color" style="color:#076be3">LETTER FROM THE <strong>SECRETARY GENERAL</strong></h2>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Dear Delegates and Faculty Advisors,</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>For eight years, The Shishukunj MUN Jhalaria Senior 2023 has been evolving and making strides in conducting the conference, and this year we are honoured to welcome you to join us for a dynamic experience. My name is Nishka Kankaria and I will be serving as the Secretary General of The Shishukunj Model United Nations this year.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>The past couple of years have been filled with challenges that have underscored the inequality and disparity in our world. With a global pandemic that has brought to light the immense resource and privilege gap along the lines of class and identity, we are forced to confront difficult questions of justice, equity, and development. This year at the Shishukunj MUN Jhalaria Senior 2023, we offer a space for the students to delve into these questions and address global issues. The students would be able to get a comprehensive experience of collaboration, learning, and personal growth, where they emerge with a deeper understanding of the challenges prevailing in the world.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>The theme for this year's conference is Emerge, Evolve, Elevate</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>A lot of countries and states in the world are in a state of havoc. As a united body of all nations, it is our obligation to bring light to all those people living in the duskiness of the crimes and disparity. We need to guide them and avail them with resources for them to emerge out of the shade. To keep them from falling into the same turmoil, it's our duty to help evolve the mindset of people to be more accepting, supporting and comforting towards them and together we can surely elevate the standards prevailing across the globe for humanity. All the agendas under the theme are constructively designed to make each one of us the guardians of the process of Emerging, Evolving and Elevating.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>I, along with the entire Secretariat and Bureau members, could not be more excited to have you as a participant in this iteration of the Shishukunj MUN Jhalaria Senior 2023. We have put all-out efforts and time to continue this treasured legacy and provide an exemplary experience.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:group {"layout":{"type":"flex","orientation":"vertical"}} -->
<div class="wp-block-group"><!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Regards,</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:image {"align":"left","id":2672,"width":160,"height":100,"scale":"cover","sizeSlug":"large","linkDestination":"none"} -->
<figure class="wp-block-image alignleft size-large is-resized"><img src="https://shishukunjmun4.files.wordpress.com/2023/06/nishka_sign-removebg-preview-edited.png" alt="" class="wp-image-2672" style="object-fit:cover;width:160px;height:100px" width="160" height="100" /></figure>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p><strong>Nishka Kankaria<br>Secretary General<br>Shishukunj MUN Senior Jhalaria 2023</strong></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph --></div>
<!-- /wp:group --></div>
<!-- /wp:group --></div>
<!-- /wp:group -->

<!-- wp:spacer {"height":"35px"} -->
<div style="height:35px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<!-- /wp:spacer -->

<!-- wp:separator {"align":"wide","className":"is-style-wide"} -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator alignwide has-alpha-channel-opacity is-style-wide" />
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:group {"align":"full","layout":{"type":"flex","flexWrap":"wrap","verticalAlignment":"top","justifyContent":"center"}} -->
<div class="wp-block-group alignfull"><!-- wp:image {"id":3855,"width":210,"height":300,"scale":"cover","sizeSlug":"large","linkDestination":"none"} -->
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large is-resized"><img src="https://shishukunjmun4.files.wordpress.com/2023/07/60a9637-1-edited.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-3855" style="object-fit:cover;width:210px;height:300px" width="210" height="300" /></figure>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:separator {"align":"wide","className":"is-style-wide"} -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator alignwide has-alpha-channel-opacity is-style-wide" />
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:group {"style":{"layout":{"selfStretch":"fixed","flexSize":"700px"}},"layout":{"type":"flex","orientation":"vertical","verticalAlignment":"top","justifyContent":"left"}} -->
<div class="wp-block-group"><!-- wp:heading {"textAlign":"right","style":{"color":{"text":"#076be3"}}} -->
<h2 class="wp-block-heading has-text-align-right has-text-color" style="color:#076be3">LETTER FROM THE <strong>DIRECTOR GENERAL</strong></h2>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>With tremendous honour and immense delight, I, Arisha Syed, as the Director General, earnestly welcome you all to the 8th iteration of the Shishukunj Model United Nations to be held from August 24 to August 26, 2023. I hope this year, the conference enhances, amplifies and strengthens the diplomat in you.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>My journey of MUNing has been incredible and soon after few conferences I got to learn that they were my niche. MUNs were not a place for me to win but to learn, explore and improve. Starting as a puzzled delegate to becoming a responsible part of Secretariat, the debating, discussing, negotiating involved in them has enhanced my personality and given me a magnified, wider perspective on global issues. They were the place I found my love for international relations, geopolitics and the place I instilled the art, the confidence of elocution. They have been pivotal in building the individual I am today.&nbsp;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>This year we bring 12 vigorous committees discussing methodical, complex agendas at a greater depth with a better focus. The committees ranging from UNCSW to Lok Sabha, from DISEC to PCIJ have been formulated pensively to give the delegates a taste of distinct yet grave agendas.&nbsp;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p><em>Everything on this earth is in a continuous state of evolving, refining, improving, adapting, enhancing and changing.&nbsp;You were not put on this earth to remain stagnant.</em></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>This years theme Emerge, Evolve, Elevate commands the path for not just a better future but an effective change. The planet is in pandemonium because humans have resorted to arms, conflicts, wars as the only means to attain their objective. Whether it be the Somalian Crisis, violence in Iran or the Palestinian refugees, the reverberations of these have only ruined lives of innocent, innocuous civilians.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>The world now demands for individuals who can change the progressions of such conflicts, by not just providing solution for alarming crises but also taking steps to implement it. The theme connotes the students to step out of their peripheries, examine, enunciate and act on the predicaments not just as their delegations but as a global citizen.&nbsp;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Every individual part of this conference will be instrumental in making it triumph.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>I hope these 3 days are full of exploration, advancement, productivity and insight. Thrilled to see you all in August!</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:image {"id":3168,"width":232,"height":128,"sizeSlug":"large","linkDestination":"none","style":{"color":[]}} -->
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large is-resized"><img src="https://shishukunjmun4.files.wordpress.com/2023/06/arisha_sign-removebg-preview-edited-1.png" alt="" class="wp-image-3168" style="width:232px;height:128px" width="232" height="128" /></figure>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p><strong>Arisha Syed<br>Director General<br>Shishukunj MUN Senior Jhalaria 2023</strong></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph --></div>
<!-- /wp:group --></div>
<!-- /wp:group -->

<!-- wp:spacer {"height":"35px"} -->
<div style="height:35px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<!-- /wp:spacer -->

<!-- wp:separator {"align":"wide","className":"is-style-wide"} -->
<hr class="wp-block-separator alignwide has-alpha-channel-opacity is-style-wide" />
<!-- /wp:separator -->

<!-- wp:group {"align":"full","layout":{"type":"flex","flexWrap":"wrap","verticalAlignment":"top","justifyContent":"center"}} -->
<div class="wp-block-group alignfull"><!-- wp:image {"id":4085,"width":210,"height":300,"scale":"cover","sizeSlug":"large","linkDestination":"none"} -->
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large is-resized"><img src="https://shishukunjmun4.files.wordpress.com/2023/07/bi25277-9-edited.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-4085" style="object-fit:cover;width:210px;height:300px" width="210" height="300" /></figure>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:group {"style":{"layout":{"selfStretch":"fixed","flexSize":"700px"}},"layout":{"type":"flex","orientation":"vertical","verticalAlignment":"top","justifyContent":"left"}} -->
<div class="wp-block-group"><!-- wp:heading {"textAlign":"right","style":{"layout":{"selfStretch":"fit","flexSize":null},"color":{"text":"#076be3"}},"fontSize":"large"} -->
<h2 class="wp-block-heading has-text-align-right has-text-color has-large-font-size" style="color:#076be3">LETTER FROM THE <strong>ASSOCIATE SECRETARY GENERAL</strong></h2>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>It gives me immense pleasure to welcome you to the eighth iteration of the Shishukunj Model United Nations Senior Jhalaria Campus. For the first time in the history of our school's MUNs has such a large-scale event been planned, with conferences spanning over two different schools. The Secretariat and the Bureau are all set to welcome you all and ensure an enriching experience for all students.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>I suddenly remember a younger version of me in seventh grade, who participated in her first MUN as a delegate, completely starstruck and clueless, not having even the slightest idea that one day she'll chair a committee and eventually become a part of the Secretariat. MUNs shaped me as a person. I came to know about world affairs around me and the problems that the earth is facing in the current generation. It gave me a sense of diplomacy and further enhanced my communication skills. It has paved my way to becoming a &nbsp;confident individual.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>During the span of this MUN, students will get a once-in-a-lifetime experience to witness worldly exposure as delegates, IP, Media or even Crisis staff members. Every person plays a crucial and pivotal role in making this MUN what it is, and in establishing its true essence.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>The theme for this year's conference urges all participants to emerge as leaders, evolve as people and elevate the state of the world from the present. My team and I are resolute in ensuring a worthwhile experience for every student and making this MUN unforgettable. Hoping to see you at&nbsp;the&nbsp;conference!</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:image {"id":2665,"width":167,"height":104,"sizeSlug":"large","linkDestination":"none"} -->
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large is-resized"><img src="https://shishukunjmun4.files.wordpress.com/2023/06/aaheli-sign-trans.png?w=720" alt="" class="wp-image-2665" style="width:167px;height:104px" width="167" height="104" /></figure>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p><strong>Aaheli Roy<br>Associate Secretary General<br>Shishukunj MUN Senior Jhalaria 2023</strong></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph --></div>
<!-- /wp:group --></div>
